You are on a stage.
You can see a microphone.
You can go west.
You are faced with a large audience. The people expect a performancce.
> switch on microphone

> switch on microphone
You turn the microphone on. Now you can start.
> tell joke

> tell joke
You start telling a joke and suddenly you feel the power of the divine jester.
It becomes easier from joke to joke and you even do some antics.

Even the lamest jokes seem to be funny enough:
"What washes up on tiny beaches?" -- "Microwaves!"
"What do you do when you see a spaceman?" -- "Park your car, man!"
"What do sharks say when something radical happens?" -- "Jawesome!"

You can see laughing children and happy people in the crowd. They are cheering to you.
Will you win the contest? In fact, it is not important. You succeeded in gaining personality, and that is all that counts.
You needn't be the best to be somebody.
The adventure ends here.
Congratulations!
